<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n01003e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01003e">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01003e"> 3(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> W thinks she is frigged in sleep / tells Priest. He at altar next / morning thinks he has been / polluted. Catechism class He / explains boy&apos;s revery. He / meets girl. She dreams / &ldquo;The glance&rdquo; </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Cf the &lsquo;glance&rsquo; motif in Wagner&apos;s Tristan, so called because it first appears prominently at Isolde&apos;s words &lsquo;er sah mir in die Augen&rsquo; near the beginning of Act One. See also <a name="n11007i" href="n11all.htm#n11007i">N11 (VI.B.5):007(i)</a>.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c05094c" href="c05all.htm#c05094c">VI.C.05:094(c)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
